reviews.review_text: I had this on a reel! About 10 years ago, an uncle of mine gave me a ton of reel to reels from a friend of his. His friend got them from a serious Dead Head who had died, and no one knew what to do with them. To make a long story short, I waded thru a ton of tapes, mostly aud stuff, (which turns most people off)and this was one of the lost treasures. I know most people go right to SBD of this show, but I for one love the aud reaction on these tapes. Anyway, this is no doubt the same source because there are pauses that cut off the start of most tunes. At least the big jam is left intact for all eternity! I think whoever taped this also taped 5-21-74. Another great aud tape.

nice there's a bit of hiss, and a few missing seconds at the start of many of the songs- but when you hear Garcia's guitar  pop from the mix- clear and hot-it's a joy.
minor adjustment needed-several song titles and files don't match...I've noticed this in other downloads...so be aware-you can't always believe what you read...
remember- quantity of downloads doesn't mean quality...and many of my favorite downloads are marred with petty/lame reviews..
like 2 stars because they had a bad trip, or they're angry about soundboards being removed...etc.
or- low in quantity because they were added recently.
on the other hand I love many of the stories-and miss those days-never felt so safe and friendly with strangers...the GD wasn't a "show" it was unbridled joy..a real good time.
thanks to all the tapers-
Hearing these aud..is like cool fresh water,
after a long day in the desert-
in 1971 I had a couple hours of GD
thanks to this wonderful site my joy and GD collection has grown a exponentially.  
thank you, thank you, thank you.

Sweet Enough This recording is awesome and the performance is really hot -- especially the guitars. Yeah, there are some flaws and minor distractions on a 40+ year old audience effort but the recordist caught the GD on a good night and the WOS sound system didn't disappoint. You can tell the difference that beautiful monstrosity made, and, hey, it's sweet enough for me. Every instrument and voice is clear and vibrant. My hat is off to Mr Lee for giving us this fine rendering.

Corrected tracklist This is a really enjoyable recording but the metadata is a mess.  

There are tracks in the wrong order, a blank track that can be deleted, and a title missing (tico tico) which is also missing from the official page on dead.net.
